After a successful email/password login, silently save the email to `userData/saved-email.json` and show a persistent toast: "Save password to Keychain?" with Save/No thanks actions. If the user chooses Save, store the password via `keytar` in the OS Keychain (visible in macOS Keychain Access under "ToDoozy"). On the next login screen load, pre-fill both fields. For Google OAuth logins, save only the email (no password prompt). On logout, clear both the saved email JSON and the Keychain entry.

